raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: A Subject Matter Expert is a recognized expert in a particular field or discipline. The Subject Matter Expert is usually brought onto a project team to provide targeted expertise that the team does not have. The Subject Matter Expert does not have direct management responsibilities for the project team staff, but serves as a thought leader to the project team.  The Subject Matter Expert is a specialist with a strong focus on a specific key technical or business area and is able to incorporate new ideas and constructs when dealing with complex problems. The Subject Matter Expert has proven leadership capabilities, can guide teams building technical and business frameworks, develop evaluation processes for product areas, and feels comfortable in a hands-on work environment. The Subject Matter Expert possesses strong written and oral communication skills, has the ability to set technical direction, and provides innovation in a fast paced multi-disciplinary environment.

raw_data.title: Senior Manager
raw_data.description: The Senior Manager provides leadership throughout the lifecycle of a project that may include direction on information technology systems architecture, development processes.  This role is responsible for guiding the design, user interface, and information technology integration of projects and interfacing with the client.  The Senior Manage also provides experienced project management capabilities, encompassing all facets of project and program management, client management, and team leadership.  This person posses strong leadership and written and oral communication skills, structures and manages integrated, multi-track projects and programs to meet overall objectives and client business drivers, and is regarded as a subject matter expert on specific information technology platform/ packages.

raw_data.title: Manager
raw_data.description: The Manager oversees the development, design, user interface, information technology integration, and site architecture management.  This role works with the client's IT organization to establish technology strategy at an application level and is responsible for managing technology teams from definition phase through implementation.  The Manager works with clients to align business goals with IT investments, measure IT investment metrics of success, and prioritize new and existing investments.  The Manager brings relationship building skills as well as leadership and team management skills to lead diverse and dynamic teams in the successful delivery of complex integrated client information technology solutions. This role requires an understanding of project management tools and approaches to manage complex, multi-disciplinary projects.  This role provides day-to-day project contact for the client (expectations, communications, negotiations, escalation, feedback, etc.) and project quality and performance standards.  This role also can also serve as the leader of creative design teams,

raw_data.title: Senior Cloud Technology Consultant
raw_data.description: The Senior Cloud Technology Consultant provides highly technical expertise and guidance with selection and implementation of cloud services and cloud-based products that utilize IaaS, PaaS, SaaS, and other cloud deployment models. The Senior Cloud Technology Consultant has specialized training and expertise and/or certifications with one or several commercial cloud providers such as Azure, AWS, or Google Cloud. Develops and applies advanced methods in the analysis, configuration, and customization of cloud solutions to meet business requirements. Provides team leadership and/or consulting support complex cloud implementations. Participates in strategy sessions, strategic assessments, and design reviews to validate enterprise approach and associated work products. Recognized for strong expertise in industry issues and trends.

raw_data.title: Cloud SME
raw_data.description: The Cloud Subject Matter Expert (SME) uses expertise gained through direct cloud implementation experience to take responsibility for the design, implementation, and management of Cloud-based projects. The Cloud SME provides leadership throughout the lifecycle of a project that may include direction on information technology, systems architecture, and development processes. Provides experienced project management capabilities, encompassing all facets of project and program management, client management, and team leadership. Structures and manages integrated, multi-track projects and programs to meet overall objectives and client business drivers. Regarded as a subject matter expert on specific information technology platform/packages. The Cloud SME has demonstrated abilities to provide guidance and direction for cloud-based projects or sub-tasks related to cloud services such as assessing cloud solutions, refactoring workloads for cloud solutions, migrating legacy or other systems to cloud solutions, providing management/governance of cloud solutions, DevSecOps, developing cloud native applications, or other cloud-oriented activities.

raw_data.title: Senior Cloud Functional Specialist
raw_data.description: The Senior Cloud Functional Specialist provides functional expertise and in-depth knowledge necessary to interpret requirements, ensure responsiveness, and achieve successful performance in a business, operational, engineering, mathematics, or scientific area. Participates in all phases of the cloud project lifecycle and advises other IT consultants with the extensive knowledge needed from the specialist for effective implementation. Expert in available state-of-the-art emerging Cloud technologies and their use in solutioning to solve complex user requirements. Analyzes, designs, and applies the knowledge needed to investigate and solution using Cloud-based technologies. Provides technical expertise and guidance in emerging Cloud technologies, plan, conduct, and technically direct implementations. The Senior Cloud Functional Specialist is often the primary day-to-day client point of contact. As such, they are involved in most if not all client communications, including the creation and delivery of presentations and leading client meetings, and ensuring project quality and performance standards are met.

raw_data.title: Cloud Functional Specialist
raw_data.description: The Cloud Functional Specialist interacts with clients on a day-to-day basis, applying their expertise to the practical issues they identify, or those presented by the client. They create cloud specifications from business and technical requirements for one or more modules within the project. The Cloud Functional Specialist applies expertise and knowledge of cloud-based software, hardware, network infrastructure, and other information technology to install, configure, maintain, and troubleshoot highly complex user/system problems. The Cloud Functional Specialist plays a variety of project support roles in DevSecOps, data/analytics, cloud migrations, management of cloud solutions, development of cloud native applications, and other cloud-related roles.

raw_data.title: Intermediate Cloud Services Associate
raw_data.description: The Intermediate Cloud Services Associate is part of the project team and may participate in the design and implementation of cloud services. This can include assessing cloud solutions, refactoring workloads for cloud solutions, migrating legacy or other systems to cloud solutions, providing management/governance of cloud solutions, DevSecOps, developing cloud native applications, or other cloud-oriented activities. The Intermediate Cloud Services Associate interacts with clients to create cloud-based specifications from business requirements for one of the modules within the project. Designs architectures that fully leverage cloud service provider services and include software and infrastructure to support the total requirements, as well as provide for present and future requirements and interfaces.

raw_data.title: Cloud Services Associate
raw_data.description: The Cloud Services Associate works as a member of a project team, performing in a variety of different roles and tasks on a client engagement. Examples of these roles include, but are not limited to: • Participating in cloud system requirements gathering, designing solutions, and creating units of deliverables (i.e., cloud native application code; requirement, design, and training artifacts; configuration designs; QA plans and reports, etc.). • Supporting the completion of cloud implementation tasks within estimated time frames and budgets. • Interfacing with the client on a day-to-day business in scheduled and ad hoc meetings and discussions.  • Delivering a wide variety of cloud solutions using skills in software development, DevSecOps, data/analytics, AI/ML, interactive design, and business/user process engineering. • Designing and building cloud standards and systems to capture, process, and analyze large quantities of health research data. The Cloud Service Associate possesses strong organizational skills, verbal, and written skills, and has completed course work in an information technology field related to cloud services.
